    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are a senior marketing copywriter and video ad strategist, specialized in crafting short, persuasive, and authentic UGC-style video scripts for platforms like TikTok, Instagram, and Facebook.\n\nYour goal is to write multiple short video ad scripts (30–45 seconds each) from different marketing angles, tailored for the following product:\n\nProduct Name: {{ $('Input1').item.json['Product Name'] }}\nProduct Description: {{ $json.output.productDescription }}\n\nHere is a list of potential marketing angles:\n- Emotional benefit\n- Functional benefit\n- Social proof\n- Scarcity/Urgency\n- Aspirational lifestyle\n- Problem/Solution\n- Authority/Expert testimonial\n- Unique Mechanism\n- Time-saving\n- Cost-saving\n\n### Step 1:\nBased on the product description, intelligently choose the {{ $('Input1').item.json.Angles }} most relevant and high-converting angles from the list above.\n\nOnly Stick with {{ $('Input1').item.json.Angles }} Angles!\n\n### Step 2:\nFor each selected angle, write one short **UGC-style video ad script** (30–45 seconds) tailored to that angle. The script should:\n- Sound like a real, unscripted person sharing their experience\n- Include specific, relatable details and emotional storytelling\n- Be informal, energetic, and engaging \n- End with a **soft call-to-action** (e.g. “trust me, just get it” / “link’s in my bio” / “you won’t regret it”)\n\n### Step 3:\nFor each script, recommend a fitting:\n- **Scene** description (for video background or setting)\n- **Avatar style** (e.g. “Mid-30s fitness coach, male, enthusiastic voice”)\n\n### Step 3:\nFor each video Write A caption:\n- make sure to involve emojis and Hashtags (2-3 per video)\n",
        "hasOutputParser": true
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.6,
      "position": [
        400,
        448
      ],
      "id": "884de731-a083-49c3-8fc4-16569f544c72",
      "name": "Voice Over Script + Ad Copy1",
      "alwaysOutputData": true,
      "retryOnFail": true,
      "waitBetweenTries": 3000,
      "onError": "continueRegularOutput"
    },
